        <li>An Info button is now available for the Commentators, which shows a modal with technical information about the Commentators default overlays</li>
        <li>Livestream Production Manager has been optimized for deployment to and running in IIS</li>
        <ul>
            <li>Url.Action() and Url.Content() are used as much as possible to make it more flexible to run in IIS</li>
            <li>It has been specifically optimized to run on the url "http://localhost/livestreamproductionmanager" in IIS</li>
            <ul>
                <li>The included default publish profile "LivestreamProductionManager.pubxml" automatically deploys to this url in IIS</li>
                <li>It is still possible to run on the url "http://localhost" with tweaks</li>
            </ul>
        </ul>
        <li>Improved the string concatenation code of the Fighting Games Manager main View, using `` instead of '' and "", resulting in shorter, easier to read concatenations</li>
        <li>The CSS selectors in the JavaScript code for managing Commentators has been slightly improved</li>
        <li>Created a Queu.css file for fading elements in overlays out and back in after updating, with the option to do use the "visibility" CSS attribute in special cases</li>
        <ul>
            <li>Implemented the new "visibility" fade out and back in, in OverlayManager.js</li>
            <ul>
                <li>This new "visibility" fade is automatically used if the updated html element has the class "specialFade"</li>
            </ul>
        </ul>
        <li>Many styling improvements have been made to the Fighting Games Main View</li>
        <ul>
            <li>Improved the styling of the monitors</li>
            <li>Improved the styling of the panel-headings in the Fighting Games Main View</li>
            <ul>
                <li>The panel-title text should now be perfectly centered</li>
                <li>The glyphicon inside the panel buttons don't use inline-styling as much anymore.</li>
            </ul>
            <li>The application now works better on smaller browser window sizes</li>
            <ul>
                <li>The usage of classes col-md-(number) have been replaced with col-xs-(number)</li>
                <li>Media queries are now used to make small corrections to styling on small resolution browser window sizes</li>
                <li>The following browser window sizes have been optimized for</li>
                <ul>
                    <li>2560 x 1440 (1440p)</li>
                    <li>1920 x 1080 (1080p)</li>
                    <li>1280 x 720 (720p), or one corner of a 1440p screen</li>
                    <li>960 x 540 (540p), or one corner of a 1080p screen</li>
                </ul>
            </ul>
        </ul>
        <li>Improved the error handling of the Fighting Games Main View</li>
        <ul>
            <li>Implemented try/catches in the Fighting Games Main View, OverlayManager.js and Snackbar.js</li>
            <li>Improved ajax.error handlers</li>
            <li>Improved the error monitor to facilitate the improved error handling</li>
            <li>Added two new snackbars to facilitate the improved error handling</li>
        </ul>
    </ul>

